<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="402" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,638,193,480]" pageId="9" pageNumber="402">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[175,279,194,215]" pageId="9" pageNumber="402">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Zaragoza" baseAuthorityYear="2003" box="[299,543,193,215]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Lucaina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bajacalifornica">
<emphasis box="[299,543,193,215]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="402">Lucaina bajacalifornica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be identified among other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DUGES" authorityYear="1879" box="[368,446,220,241]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Lucaina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[368,446,220,241]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="402">Lucaina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the short rostrum and labrum with curved mandibles (
<figureCitation box="[514,586,247,268]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[175,214,864,883]" captionTargetBox="[156,1167,197,847]" captionTargetId="figure-226@3.[154,1169,194,849]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 8–13. Lucaina species, head, frontal view. 8) L. schini (lectotype photograph from UNAM, used with permission); 9) L. marginata (lectotype); 10) L. discoidalis (lectotype photograph from MCZC, used with permission, ©President and Fellows of Harvard College); 11) L. bajacalifornica (holotype photograph from UNAM, used with permission); 12) L. greeni (holotype); 13) L. milleri." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4789176" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4789176/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="402">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
), the pronotum mostly black with median lateral margins yellow (
<figureCitation box="[229,287,300,321]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[197,236,1615,1634]" captionTargetBox="[229,1133,196,1597]" captionTargetId="figure-0@2.[227,1138,194,1599]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1–7. Lucaina species, dorsal habitus. 1) L. schini (lectotype photograph from UNAM, used with permission); 2) L. marginata (lectotype); 3) L. discoidalis (lectotype photograph from MCZC, used with permission, ©President and Fellows of Harvard College); 4) L. bajacalifornica (holotype photograph from UNAM, used with permission); 5) L. greeni (holotype); 6) L. greeni (bluish black elytra); 7) L. milleri." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4789158" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4789158/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="402">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); and by the parameres parallel sided in basal portion, fusiform in apical portion, and apex of median lobe narrow (
<figureCitation box="[386,458,353,374]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[197,236,1087,1106]" captionTargetBox="[177,1188,196,1069]" captionTargetId="figure-129@4.[175,1190,194,1071]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 16–21. Lucaina species, male genitalia, ventral and dorsal views, respectively. 16) L. schini; 17) L. marginata; 18) L. discoidalis; 19) L. bajacalifornica (holotype photograph from UNAM); 20) L. greeni; 21) L. milleri." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4789204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4789204/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="402">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
